\begin_layout Enumerate
[projections and orthonormal vectors] Let 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 be the subspace spanned by the orthonormal vectors 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset

.
 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 be the projection of the vector 
\begin_inset Formula $v$
\end_inset

 into 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

.
 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $r=v-p$
\end_inset

 be the residual vector.
 Then 
\begin_inset Formula $r\perp S$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ r,a,b\right\} $
\end_inset

 form an orthonormal set.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
[linear ridge regression] Given some data 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(x_{1},y_{1}\right),\ldots,\left(x_{n},y_{n}\right)\in\reals^{d}\times\reals$
\end_inset

, the ridge regression solution for regularization parameter 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda>0$
\end_inset

 is given by
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\hat{w}=\argmin_{w\in\reals^{d}}\frac{1}{n}\sum_{i=1}^{n}\left\{ w^{T}x_{i}-y_{i}\right\} ^{2}+\lambda\|w\|_{2}^{2},
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\|w\|_{2}^{2}=w_{1}^{2}+\cdots+w_{d}^{2}$
\end_inset

 is the square of the 
\begin_inset Formula $\ell_{2}$
\end_inset

-norm.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
[completing the square] You should be able to verify, just by multiplying
 out the expressions on the RHS, that the following 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

completing the square
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 identity is true: For any vectors 
\begin_inset Formula $x,b\in\reals^{d}$
\end_inset

 and symmetric invertible matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $M\in\reals^{d\times d}$
\end_inset

, we have 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray}
x^{T}Mx-2b^{T}x & = & \left(x-M^{-1}b\right)^{T}M(x-M^{-1}b)-b^{T}M^{-1}b\label{eq:second-quad-form}
\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset


\end_layout

