\begin_layout Enumerate
[directional derivative] If we fix a direction 
\begin_inset Formula $u\in\reals^{d}$
\end_inset

, we can compute the directional derivative 
\begin_inset Formula $f'(x;u)$
\end_inset

 as
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f'(x;u)=\lim_{h\to0}\frac{f(x+hu)-f(x)}{h}.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
[the risk functional] For 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

loss
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 function 
\begin_inset Formula $\ell:\cy\times\cy\to\reals$
\end_inset

, define the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
